<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>What dos the staff give?</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Mirabilis Dictu</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-21 15:23:53</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>The staff gives +5 mana to Wizards only *shrug* and is not listed as a magic item.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Olamina</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-09-09 19:22:48</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>And what do you do if you can't get Josper (or ANY npc's) to talk to you? I don't think my faction is a problem. I train there and I've killed a couple poachers and heretic prophets in toxx...of course I am a newbie so I may be way off with how faction is determined. Anyway, it is ANNOYING. Any help would be appreciated.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Olamina</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-09-11 02:27:41</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Okay, so I finally got Josper to talk to me by saying "I am a servant of wizardry."  Usually you have to phrase stuff in question form, but not this time. So I got a backpack from him and I was off to everfrost. I got there and I looked ALL over the place for ice goblin casters, but found none. Some people told me they were in Perma Frost, but I didn't go check, I just camped out a couple of ice goblin igloos and killed WHELPS and SCOUTS. They kept giving me GOBLIN ICE NECKLACES, which it turns out is what you NEED.  (I don't know where they got "goblin ice beads from goblin casters." Also I didn't see any cracked or broken "beads," AND these goblin ice necklaces were not rare at all.)  So I collected six necklaces in Josper's backpack and hit the combine button, which turned it into a bag of ice necklaces or something to that effect. I took it back to Josper and he gave me 2 gold and the 1-H blunt +5 mana Servant's Staff. This was really an easy quest. I did it at level 5. The hardest part was not getting killed by the vengeful soloist on the way out, so watch out for him and be careful going through blackburrow. GOOD LUCK!</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Firiel</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-10-12 18:33:58</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>The Goblin Caster beads are a VERY rare drop by goblin casters, at the igloos in the planes, they are a rare spawn them selves, the Goblin Ice Necklaces are a commin drop by all three goblins that spawn in EF, and are also used for a quest given in the warriors guild in Halas.</font></td></tr></table>
